1.translation-en: You will jump over the log.

5.translation-en: OK , I will/can jump that one.

notes: example - response to basic question (What is your name?)

15.translation-en: Who is that man? (What is that man called, e.g. accusative in S13 this document.)

18.translation-en: OK, I throw away this message stick.

20.translation-en: They are sending us a message stick.

21.translation-en: I think we will look for your boomerang.

22.translation-en: I will look for his boomerang.

23.full_text: wankinga barninyi nganyi wankinga nhungka bakarranyianga
23.translation-en: I looked, I couldn't find his boomerang.

24.translation-en: That group of women are having a fight.

25.translation-en: The day before yesterday the women all fought.

26.translation-en: Tomorrow the women will all fight (together).

27.full_text: wiyiani nhaniguru marrigala/ dhupuanha ngathu wupigala
27.translation-en: This fire is burning. I smell smoke.

28.translation-en: The woman is scolding this child.

29.translation-en: Cover up this kangaroo with ashes.

30.translation-en: OK, I will cover this meat.

33.translation-en: That man is telling a lie.

37.translation-en: Put (it) on the ground over there.

38.translation-en: OK, I put (it) over there on the ground.

40.translation-en: OK, I will hold (it) for you.

41.full_text: dumpa nganha nhanhaguru bakarranyinha/ ngathu nadyarra
41.translation-en: Show me that boomerang, I want to see it.

42.full_text: walya ngathu inha dumparra/ walya gadha ngathu mulpagala
42.translation-en: I will not show you, I haven't finished (it) yet.

43.translation-en: I think the two of us will hide over there.

44.translation-en: Here look out quick for kangaroos.

46.full_text: makurra nhaniguru buligaliani gurrgalanga wirlidhirra bari ngalingu
46.translation-en: A stick fell in the road. (A stick has fallen on the road.) The two of us will drag it away I think.

47.translation-en: Look out one might fall on you.

49.full_text: makurrani nhaniyi garlgugarlgunhani/ guntutyirri nhani bari bulirra
49.translation-en: This stick is rotten. I think it will fall soon. (This stick is rotten so I think it will fall.)

51.translation-en: Look out, it might bite you.

53.full_text: gari walya yanhtha/ nadyarra ngathu inha
53.translation-en: Hey don't go away, I want to see you.

54.full_text: gari bura nhanhaguru nadyarra ngathu nhanha
54.translation-en: Hey, tell that one I want to see him.

57.full_text: gala bula bura nadyarra ngathu nhanha
57.translation-en: Hey you two, tell (him) I want to see him.

58.full_text: murra ngathu buranga nhanha/ gulharra nhani/ yundru nadyarra nhanha
58.translation-en: OK, I told him, he will wait, you will see him.

60.translation-en: You will follow me. (Repeated twice in original corpus.)

62.full_text: walya ngathu nhanhaguru gangalangu/ gumiani nhaniguru
62.translation-en: I cannot carry this. It is big.

63.full_text: ga ngathu inha walibarra/ ngalingu barrkululu ganggarra nhanhaguru
63.translation-en: Yes I will help you. The two of us will carry this one.
